						<p><hi rend="bold">Chōḻa, Parakesarivarman, Year 12 = c. 11th Century.</hi> </p>						

						<p>This is damaged. It seems to record a gift of 26 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold by one Uttaman Gaṇavadi, which was entrusted to the body know as <hi rend="italic">Chōṇāṭṭu-Perumakkaḷ</hi>, for feeding Brahmanas on the hill on festival days in the month of Masi.</p>						

						<p>[Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi> Vol XIX No. 298.]</p>						

